{"$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/master/Schemata/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json","version": "2.1.0","runs": [{"tool": {"driver": {"name": "dependency-check","version": "12.1.8","informationUri": "https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/","rules": [{"id": "CVE-2025-50151","shortDescription": {"text": "high severity - CVE-2025-50151 Improper Input Validation vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.jena\/jena-arq@4.10.0"},"fullDescription": {"text": "File access paths in configuration files uploaded by users with administrator access are not validated.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Jena version up to 5.4.0.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 5.5.0, which does not allow arbitrary configuration upload."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-50151](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-50151).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 8.8,"security-severity": "8.8","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "LOW","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "HIGH","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "2.8","cvssv3_impactScore": "5.9","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-31672","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2025-31672 Improper Input Validation vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.poi\/poi@5.2.5"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Improper Input Validation vulnerability in Apache POI. The issue affects the parsing of OOXML format files like xlsx, docx and pptx. These file formats are basically zip files and it is possible for malicious users to add zip entries with duplicate names (including the path) in the zip. In this case, products reading the affected file could read different data because 1 of the zip entries with the duplicate name is selected over another but different products may choose a different zip entry.\nThis issue affects Apache POI poi-ooxml before 5.4.0. poi-ooxml 5.4.0 has a check that throws an exception if zip entries with duplicate file names are found in the input file.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version poi-ooxml 5.4.0, which fixes the issue. Please read  https:\/\/poi.apache.org\/security.html  for recommendations about how to use the POI libraries securely."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-31672](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-31672).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 5.3,"security-severity": "5.3","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "LOW","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "3.9","cvssv3_impactScore": "1.4","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-68384","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2025-68384 Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in pkg:maven\/co.elastic.clients\/elasticsearch-java@8.13.4"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling (CWE-770) in Elasticsearch can allow a low-privileged authenticated user to cause Excessive Allocation (CAPEC-130) causing a persistent denial of service (OOM crash) via submission of oversized user settings data."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-68384](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-68384).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 6.5,"security-severity": "6.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "LOW","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "2.8","cvssv3_impactScore": "3.6","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-37731","shortDescription": {"text": "high severity - CVE-2025-37731 Improper Authentication vulnerability in pkg:maven\/co.elastic.clients\/elasticsearch-java@8.13.4"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Improper Authentication in Elasticsearch PKI realm can lead to user impersonation via specially crafted client certificates. A malicious actor would need to have such a crafted client certificate signed by a legitimate, trusted Certificate Authority."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-37731](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-37731).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 7.4,"security-severity": "7.4","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "HIGH","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "HIGH","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "2.2","cvssv3_impactScore": "5.2","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-68161","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2025-68161 Improper Certificate Validation vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.logging.log4j\/log4j-api@2.23.1"},"fullDescription": {"text": "The Socket Appender in Apache Log4j Core versions 2.0-beta9 through 2.25.2 does not perform TLS hostname verification of the peer certificate, even when the  verifyHostName https:\/\/logging.apache.org\/log4j\/2.x\/manual\/appenders\/network.html#SslConfiguration-attr-verifyHostName  configuration attribute or the  log4j2.sslVerifyHostName https:\/\/logging.apache.org\/log4j\/2.x\/manual\/systemproperties.html#log4j2.sslVerifyHostName  system property is set to true.\n\nThis issue may allow a man-in-the-middle attacker to intercept or redirect log traffic under the following conditions:\n\n  *  The attacker is able to intercept or redirect network traffic between the client and the log receiver.\n  *  The attacker can present a server certificate issued by a certification authority trusted by the Socket Appender\u2019s configured trust store (or by the default Java trust store if no custom trust store is configured).\n\n\nUsers are advised to upgrade to Apache Log4j Core version 2.25.3, which addresses this issue.\n\nAs an alternative mitigation, the Socket Appender may be configured to use a private or restricted trust root to limit the set of trusted certificates."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-68161](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-68161).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 4.8,"security-severity": "4.8","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "HIGH","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "LOW","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "LOW","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "2.2","cvssv3_impactScore": "2.5","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","cvssv4_baseScore": 6.3,"security-severity": "6.3","cvssv4_vector": "CVSS:4.0\/AV:N\/AC:H\/AT:N\/PR:N\/UI:N\/VC:L\/VI:N\/VA:N\/SC:N\/SI:L\/SA:N\/E:X\/CR:X\/IR:X\/AR:X\/MAV:X\/MAC:X\/MAT:X\/MPR:X\/MUI:X\/MVC:X\/MVI:X\/MVA:X\/MSC:X\/MSI:X\/MSA:X\/S:X\/AU:X\/R:N\/V:X\/RE:X\/U:X","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2024-47554","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2024-47554 Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in pkg:maven\/commons-io\/commons-io@2.7"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in Apache Commons IO.\n\nThe org.apache.commons.io.input.XmlStreamReader class may excessively consume CPU resources when processing maliciously crafted input.\n\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons IO: from 2.0 before 2.14.0.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 2.14.0 or later, which fixes the issue."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2024-47554](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2024-47554).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 4.3,"security-severity": "4.3","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "REQUIRED","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "LOW","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "2.8","cvssv3_impactScore": "1.4","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2024-26308","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2024-26308 Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.commons\/commons-compress@1.24.0"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling vulnerability in Apache Commons Compress.This issue affects Apache Commons Compress: from 1.21 before 1.26.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 1.26, which fixes the issue."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2024-26308](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2024-26308).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 5.5,"security-severity": "5.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "LOCAL","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "REQUIRED","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "1.8","cvssv3_impactScore": "3.6","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2024-52979","shortDescription": {"text": "high severity - CVE-2024-52979 Uncontrolled Resource Consumption vulnerability in pkg:maven\/co.elastic.clients\/elasticsearch-java@8.13.4"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Uncontrolled Resource Consumption in Elasticsearch while evaluating specifically crafted search templates with Mustache functions can lead to Denial of Service by causing the Elasticsearch node to crash."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2024-52979](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2024-52979).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,"security-severity": "7.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "HIGH","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "3.9","cvssv3_impactScore": "3.6","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2024-25710","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2024-25710 Loop with Unreachable Exit Condition ('Infinite Loop') vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.commons\/commons-compress@1.24.0"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Loop with Unreachable Exit Condition ('Infinite Loop') vulnerability in Apache Commons Compress.This issue affects Apache Commons Compress: from 1.3 through 1.25.0.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 1.26.0 which fixes the issue."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2024-25710](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2024-25710).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 5.5,"security-severity": "5.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "LOCAL","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "REQUIRED","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "MEDIUM","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "1.8","cvssv3_impactScore": "3.6","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-7962","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2025-7962 Improper Neutralization of Input Terminators vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.eclipse.angus\/angus-activation@2.0.0"},"fullDescription": {"text": "In Jakarta Mail 2.0.2 it is possible to preform a SMTP Injection by utilizing the\u00A0\\r and \\n UTF-8 characters to separate different messages."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-7962](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-7962).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,"security-severity": "7.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "NONE","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "NONE","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "HIGH","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "3.9","cvssv3_impactScore": "3.6","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","cvssv4_baseScore": 6.0,"security-severity": "6.0","cvssv4_vector": "CVSS:4.0\/AV:N\/AC:H\/AT:N\/PR:L\/UI:N\/VC:N\/VI:H\/VA:N\/SC:N\/SI:L\/SA:N\/E:X\/CR:X\/IR:X\/AR:X\/MAV:X\/MAC:X\/MAT:X\/MPR:X\/MUI:X\/MVC:X\/MVI:X\/MVA:X\/MSC:X\/MSI:X\/MSA:X\/S:X\/AU:X\/R:N\/V:X\/RE:X\/U:X","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-5222","shortDescription": {"text": "high severity - CVE-2025-5222 Buffer Copy without Checking Size of Input ('Classic Buffer Overflow') vulnerability in pkg:maven\/com.ibm.icu\/icu4j@72.1"},"fullDescription": {"text": "A stack buffer overflow was found in Internationl components for unicode (ICU ). While running the genrb binary, the 'subtag' struct overflowed at the SRBRoot::addTag function. This issue may lead to memory corruption and local arbitrary code execution."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-5222](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-5222).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 7.0,"security-severity": "7.0","cvssv3_attackVector": "LOCAL","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "HIGH","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv3_userInteraction": "REQUIRED","cvssv3_scope": "UNCHANGED","cvssv3_confidentialityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_integrityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_availabilityImpact": "HIGH","cvssv3_baseSeverity": "HIGH","cvssv3_exploitabilityScore": "1.0","cvssv3_impactScore": "5.9","cvssv3_version": "_3_1","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2010-0538","shortDescription": {"text": "medium severity - CVE-2010-0538 Resource Management Errors vulnerability in pkg:maven\/com.apple\/AppleJavaExtensions@1.4"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Apple Java for Mac OS X 10.5 before Update 7 and Java for Mac OS X 10.6 before Update 2 do not properly handle mediaLibImage objects, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds memory access and application crash) via a crafted applet, related to the com.sun.medialib.mlib package."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2010-0538](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2010-0538).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv2_score": 6.8,"cvssv2_accessVector": "NETWORK","cvssv2_accessComplexity": "MEDIUM","cvssv2_authenticationr": "NONE","cvssv2_confidentialityImpact": "PARTIAL","cvssv2_integrityImpact": "PARTIAL","cvssv2_availabilityImpact": "PARTIAL","cvssv2_severity": "MEDIUM","source": "NVD"}},{"id": "CVE-2025-49656","shortDescription": {"text": "high severity - CVE-2025-49656 Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal') vulnerability in pkg:maven\/org.apache.jena\/jena-arq@4.10.0"},"fullDescription": {"text": "Users with administrator access can create databases files outside the files area of the Fuseki server.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Jena version up to 5.4.0.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 5.5.0, which fixes the issue."},"help": {"text": "","markdown": "For more information see [CVE-2025-49656](https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2025-49656).\n\n\nIf this is a false positive - consider using the HTML report to generate a suppression file. For more information see [How dependency-check works](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/internals.html),[How to read the HTML report](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/thereport.html), and[Suppressing false positives](https://dependency-check.github.io/DependencyCheck/general/suppression.html)."},"properties": {"cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,"security-severity": "7.5","cvssv3_attackVector": "NETWORK","cvssv3_attackComplexity": "LOW","cvssv3_privilegesRequired": "NONE","cvssv