asticsearch, where a large recursion using the innerForbidCircularReferences function of the PatternBank class could cause the Elasticsearch node to crash.\n\nA successful attack requires a malicious user to have read_pipeline Elasticsearch cluster privilege assigned to them."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "d57f13bda6dcb41799e00aa830e41592"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.elasticsearch.client\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer\/8.13.4\/b65d6f3754dd9732d36297074eca37a130c02e5e\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer-8.13.4.jar","index": 161 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.elasticsearch.client\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer@8.13.4"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-68384","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-68384 - Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling (CWE-770) in Elasticsearch can allow a low-privileged authenticated user to cause Excessive Allocation (CAPEC-130) causing a persistent denial of service (OOM crash) via submission of oversized user settings data."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "ac51d008ef04c6ed430a81784f41f38a"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.elasticsearch.client\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer\/8.13.4\/b65d6f3754dd9732d36297074eca37a130c02e5e\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer-8.13.4.jar","index": 161 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.elasticsearch.client\/elasticsearch-rest-client-sniffer@8.13.4"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-37727","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-37727 - Insertion of sensitive information in log file in Elasticsearch can lead to loss of confidentiality under specific preconditions when auditing requests to the  reindex API https:\/\/www.elastic.co\/docs\/api\/doc\/elasticsearch\/operation\/operatio