e subject to denial of service (DOS) attacks when using the expression evaluator.guess parameter name method. If the parser runs on user-supplied input, an attacker could supply content that causes the parser to crash due to a stack overflow. NOTE: this is disputed by multiple parties because Janino is not intended for use with untrusted input."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "990b73744f169f883187873dcc3856cf"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.openapitools\/openapi-generator-cli\/7.18.0\/8bd615a50b15ebf5be30e612af112526a6e81ac4\/openapi-generator-cli-7.18.0.jar\/META-INF\/maven\/org.codehaus.janino\/commons-compiler\/pom.xml","index": 570 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.codehaus.janino\/commons-compiler@3.1.9"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-33546","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-33546 - Janino 3.1.9 and earlier are subject to denial of service (DOS) attacks when using the expression evaluator.guess parameter name method. If the parser runs on user-supplied input, an attacker could supply content that causes the parser to crash due to a stack overflow. NOTE: this is disputed by multiple parties because Janino is not intended for use with untrusted input."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "990b73744f169f883187873dcc3856cf"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.openapitools\/openapi-generator-cli\/7.18.0\/8bd615a50b15ebf5be30e612af112526a6e81ac4\/openapi-generator-cli-7.18.0.jar\/META-INF\/maven\/org.codehaus.janino\/janino\/pom.xml","index": 571 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.codehaus.janino\/janino@3.1.9"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-6298","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-6298 - A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in Apryse iText 8.0.2. This vulnerability affects the function main of the file PdfDocument.java. The manipulation leads to improper validation of array index. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. The real existence of this vulnerability is still doubted at the moment. The identifier of this vulnerability is VDB-246124. NOTE: The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way. A statement published afterwards explains that the exception is not a vulnerability and the identified CWEs might not apply to the software."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "5c349c1386f9a89fb06ba5f675e93ba2"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/com.itextpdf\/pdfa\/8.0.2\/95181451649f04fc889bda20a41e1ef0de865c95\/pdfa-8.0.2.jar","index": 638 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/com.itextpdf\/pdfa@8.0.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2026-0858","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2026-0858 - Versions of the package net.sourceforge.plantuml:plantuml before 1.2026.0 are vulnerable to Stored XSS due to insufficient sanitization of interactive attributes in GraphViz diagrams. As a result, a crafted PlantUML diagram can inject malicious JavaScript into generated SVG output, leading to arbitrary script execution in the context of applications that render the SVG."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "48ceb1d6907313334c35cc7ffaf7801c"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/net.sourceforge.plantuml\/plantuml-mit\/1.2023.9\/6ca77dd474eae7a2a1581e4b236ede5515ae25a7\/plantuml-mit-1.2023.9.jar","index": 656 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/net.sourceforge.plantuml\/plantuml-mit@1.2023.9"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-31672","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-31672 - Improper Input Validation vulnerability in Apache POI. The issue affects the parsing of OOXML format files like xlsx, docx and pptx. These file formats are basically zip files and it is possible for malicious users to add zip entries with duplicate names (including the path) in the zip. In this case, products reading the affected file could read different data because 1 of the zip entries with the duplicate name is selected over another but different products may choose a different zip entry.\nThis issue affects Apache POI poi-ooxml before 5.4.0. poi-ooxml 5.4.0 has a check that throws an exception if zip entries with duplicate file names are found in the input file.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version poi-ooxml 5.4.0, which fixes the issue. Please read  https:\/\/poi.apache.org\/security.html  for recommendations about how to use the POI libraries securely."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "6e558e89e1b207165384eb838b0d61b8"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.apache.poi\/poi\/5.2.5\/7e00f6b2f76375fe89022d5a7db8acb71cbd55f5\/poi-5.2.5.jar","index": 659 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.apache.poi\/poi@5.2.5"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-31672","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-31672 - Improper Input Validation vulnerability in Apache POI. The issue affects the parsing of OOXML format files like xlsx, docx and pptx. These file formats are basically zip files and it is possible for malicious users to add zip entries with duplicate names (including the path) in the zip. In this case, products reading the affected file could read different data because 1 of the zip entries with the duplicate name is selected over another but different products may choose a different zip entry.\nThis issue affects Apache POI poi-ooxml before 5.4.0. poi-ooxml 5.4.0 has a check that throws an exception if zip entries with duplicate file names are found in the input file.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version poi-ooxml 5.4.0, which fixes the issue. Please read  https:\/\/poi.apache.org\/security.html  for recommendations about how to use the POI libraries securely."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "6e558e89e1b207165384eb838b0d61b8"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.apache.poi\/poi-ooxml\/5.2.5\/df9f2c52371eeba24db8ea8cafa77285c3cc0742\/poi-ooxml-5.2.5.jar","index": 660 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.apache.poi\/poi-ooxml@5.2.5"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-31672","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-31672 - Improper Input Validation vulnerability in Apache POI. The issue affects the parsing of OOXML format files like xlsx, docx and pptx. These file formats are basically zip files and it is possible for malicious users to add zip entries with duplicate names (including the path) in the zip. In this case, products reading the affected file could read different data because 1 of the zip entries with the duplicate name is selected over another but different products may choose a different zip entry.\nThis issue affects Apache POI poi-ooxml before 5.4.0. poi-ooxml 5.4.0 has a check that throws an exception if zip entries with duplicate file names are found in the input file.\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version poi-ooxml 5.4.0, which fixes the issue. Please read  https:\/\/poi.apache.org\/security.html  for recommendations about how to use the POI libraries securely."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "6e558e89e1b207165384eb838b0d61b8"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.apache.poi\/poi-ooxml-lite\/5.2.5\/eaa61452d8f0d13080fbb4757a392f09f90e4c49\/poi-ooxml-lite-5.2.5.jar","index": 661 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.apache.poi\/poi-ooxml-lite@5.2.5"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2024-7254","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2024-7254 - Any project that parses untrusted Protocol Buffers data\u00A0containing an arbitrary number of nested groups \/ series of SGROUP\u00A0tags can corrupted by exceeding the stack limit i.e. StackOverflow. Parsing nested groups as unknown fields with DiscardUnknownFieldsParser or Java Protobuf Lite parser, or against Protobuf map fields, creates unbounded recursions that can be abused by an attacker."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "b2bef45f1f825e34b3d1de10141de7bc"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/com.google.protobuf\/protobuf-java\/3.24.3\/8e0f08a59c21e3f17121667489a005a8df091af0\/protobuf-java-3.24.3.jar","index": 673 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/com.google.protobuf\/protobuf-java@3.24.3"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-6298","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-6298 - A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in Apryse iText 8.0.2. This vulnerability affects the function main of the file PdfDocument.java. The manipulation leads to improper validation of array index. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. The real existence of this vulnerability is still doubted at the moment. The identifier of this vulnerability is VDB-246124. NOTE: The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way. A statement published afterwards explains that the exception is not a vulnerability and the identified CWEs might not apply to the software."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "5c349c1386f9a89fb06ba5f675e93ba2"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/com.itextpdf\/sign\/8.0.2\/af6d8a9efd7757931a5426ca32831113d9191d5c\/sign-8.0.2.jar","index": 725 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/com.itextpdf\/sign@8.0.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-34055","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-34055 - In Spring Boot versions 2.7.0 - 2.7.17, 3.0.0-3.0.12 and 3.1.0-3.1.5, it is possible for a user to provide specially crafted HTTP requests that may cause a denial-of-service (DoS) condition.\n\nSpecifically, an application is vulnerable when all of the following are true:\n\n  *  the application uses Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux\n  *  org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator\u00A0is on the classpath"},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "063b1abf80a94f97750f4ab3a0ce4090"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.springframework.boot\/spring-boot\/3.1.2\/3cf070561716277ec91ebadc07362dd0b4a9f63f\/spring-boot-3.1.2.jar","index": 737 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.springframework.boot\/spring-boot@3.1.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-34055","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-34055 - In Spring Boot versions 2.7.0 - 2.7.17, 3.0.0-3.0.12 and 3.1.0-3.1.5, it is possible for a user to provide specially crafted HTTP requests that may cause a denial-of-service (DoS) condition.\n\nSpecifically, an application is vulnerable when all of the following are true:\n\n  *  the application uses Spring MVC or Spring WebFlux\n  *  org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator\u00A0is on the classpath"},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "063b1abf80a94f97750f4ab3a0ce4090"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.springframework.boot\/spring-boot-autoconfigure\/3.1.2\/ea294976f925441fc1d5a5414d5d31717f06aa3c\/spring-boot-autoconfigure-3.1.2.jar","index": 741 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/org.springframework.boot\/spring-boot-autoconfigure@3.1.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-6298","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-6298 - A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in Apryse iText 8.0.2. This vulnerability affects the function main of the file PdfDocument.java. The manipulation leads to improper validation of array index. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. The real existence of this vulnerability is still doubted at the moment. The identifier of this vulnerability is VDB-246124. NOTE: The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way. A statement published afterwards explains that the exception is not a vulnerability and the identified CWEs might not apply to the software."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "5c349c1386f9a89fb06ba5f675e93ba2"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/com.itextpdf\/styled-xml-parser\/8.0.2\/de321f92c7d7e09a6425a0101f58e3e07f0a9ab3\/styled-xml-parser-8.0.2.jar","index": 844 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/com.itextpdf\/styled-xml-parser@8.0.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2023-6298","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2023-6298 - A vulnerability classified as problematic was found in Apryse iText 8.0.2. This vulnerability affects the function main of the file PdfDocument.java. The manipulation leads to improper validation of array index. The attack can be initiated remotely. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used. The real existence of this vulnerability is still doubted at the moment. The identifier of this vulnerability is VDB-246124. NOTE: The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way. A statement published afterwards explains that the exception is not a vulnerability and the identified CWEs might not apply to the software."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "5c349c1386f9a89fb06ba5f675e93ba2"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/com.itextpdf\/svg\/8.0.2\/4311f6d379b3f84eedc56c66f4cd586104d9d089\/svg-8.0.2.jar","index": 845 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:maven\/com.itextpdf\/svg@8.0.2"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-26791","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-26791 - DOMPurify before 3.2.4 has an incorrect template literal regular expression, sometimes leading to mutation cross-site scripting (mXSS)."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "e82ad5296ac88f8be4c6f80f1ded9d8a"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.webjars\/swagger-ui\/5.17.14\/7c746d197424eb721b4e08fcaa9e85231662d81f\/swagger-ui-5.17.14.jar\/META-INF\/resources\/webjars\/swagger-ui\/5.17.14\/swagger-ui-bundle.js","index": 870 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:javascript\/DOMPurify@3.1.4"}]}]}, {"ruleId": "CVE-2025-26791","level": "warning","message": {"text": "CVE-2025-26791 - DOMPurify before 3.2.4 has an incorrect template literal regular expression, sometimes leading to mutation cross-site scripting (mXSS)."},"partialFingerprints": {"vulnerabilityHash": "e82ad5296ac88f8be4c6f80f1ded9d8a"},"locations": [{"physicalLocation": {"artifactLocation": {"uri": "file://\/home\/webemo-aaron\/.gradle\/caches\/modules-2\/files-2.1\/org.webjars\/swagger-ui\/5.17.14\/7c746d197424eb721b4e08fcaa9e85231662d81f\/swagger-ui-5.17.14.jar\/META-INF\/resources\/webjars\/swagger-ui\/5.17.14\/swagger-ui-es-bundle.js","index": 872 }},"logicalLocations": [{"fullyQualifiedName": "pkg:javascript\/DOMPurify@3.1.4"}]}]}]}]}